name: UnmodifiableListView
comment:
An unmodifiable dart-core.List view of another List.

The source of the elements may be a dart-core.List or any dart-core.Iterable with efficient dart-core.Iterable.length and dart-core.Iterable.elementAt.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

[].comment: Returns the object at the given dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.[].index in the list or throws a dart-core.RangeError if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.[].index is out of bounds.

length=.name: length=
length=.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

reversed.name: reversed
reversed.comment: Returns an dart-core.Iterable of the objects in this list in reverse order.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

[].comment: Returns the object at the given dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.[].index in the list or throws a dart-core.RangeError if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.[].index is out of bounds.

[]=.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.map.f multiple times on the same element.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.where.test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.where.test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.where.test multiple times on the same element.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.contains.element.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.every.test. Returns false otherwise.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.join.separator string.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.any.test. Returns false otherwise.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.take.n elements.

It is an error if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.elementAt.indexth element.

The dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than dart-core.Iterable.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.elementAt.index elements in this.

add.name: add
add.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

sort.name: sort
sort.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

shuffle.name: shuffle
shuffle.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

indexOf.name: indexOf
indexOf.comment:
Returns the first index of dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.indexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list from index dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.indexOf.start to the end of the list. The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.indexOf('re');    // 1
notes.indexOf('re', 2); // 3

Returns -1 if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.indexOf.element is not found.

notes.indexOf('fa');    // -1

lastIndexOf.name: lastIndexOf
lastIndexOf.comment:
Returns the last index of dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list backwards from index dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.start to 0.

The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.lastIndexOf('re', 2); // 1

If dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.start is not provided, this method searches from the end of the list./Returns

notes.lastIndexOf('re');  // 3

Returns -1 if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.element is not found.

notes.lastIndexOf('fa');  // -1

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

insert.name: insert
insert.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

insertAll.name: insertAll
insertAll.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

setAll.name: setAll
setAll.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

removeAt.name: removeAt
removeAt.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

removeLast.name: removeLast
removeLast.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

sublist.name: sublist
sublist.comment:
Returns a new list containing the objects from dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.start inclusive to dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.end exclusive.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
colors.sublist(1, 3); // ['green', 'blue']

If dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.end is omitted, the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.length of this is used.

colors.sublist(1);  // ['green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink']

An error occurs if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.start is outside the range 0 .. length or if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.end is outside the range start .. length.

getRange.name: getRange
getRange.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable that iterates over the objects in the range dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.start inclusive to dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.end exclusive.

An error occurs if dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.end is before dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.start.

An error occurs if the dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.start and dart-collection.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.end are not valid ranges at the time of the call to this method. The returned dart-core.Iterable behaves like skip(start).take(end - start). That is, it does not throw exceptions if this changes size.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
Iterable<String> range = colors.getRange(1, 4);
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue, orange'
colors.length = 3;
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue'

setRange.name: setRange
setRange.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

removeRange.name: removeRange
removeRange.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

fillRange.name: fillRange
fillRange.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

replaceRange.name: replaceRange
replaceRange.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

asMap.name: asMap
asMap.comment:
Returns an unmodifiable dart-core.Map view of this.

The map uses the indices of this list as keys and the corresponding objects as values. The Map.keys dart-core.Iterable iterates the indices of this list in numerical order.

List<String> words = ['fee', 'fi', 'fo', 'fum'];
Map<int, String> map = words.asMap();
map[0] + map[1];   // 'feefi';
map.keys.toList(); // [0, 1, 2, 3]
